Analysis, publication and impact work is ongoing.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Press officers and academics will amend press release practices. We are developing training courses and guidelines in collaboration with press officers.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>036DFA09-D7FE-4ADD-B716-1964B2257EA7</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>56dde37e887556.15932343</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Communities and Social Services/Policy,Creative Economy,Education,Environment,Healthcare,Other</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>6A5799FE-BD5D-4055-AA64-E13F73BB8371</gtr:id><gtr:title>Exaggerations and Caveats in Press Releases and Health-Related Science News.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>PloS one</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/3311e41e9e118b98b6665173e9ba7b3f"><gtr:id>3311e41e9e118b98b6665173e9ba7b3f</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Sumner P</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2016-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1932-6203</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>58c2724b321028.94163541</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>DADD5ED6-DEEB-43B3-9792-2EBADE922008</gtr:id><gtr:title>The association between exaggeration in health related science news and academic press releases: retrospective observational study.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>BMJ (Clinical research ed.)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/3311e41e9e118b98b6665173e9ba7b3f"><gtr:id>3311e41e9e118b98b6665173e9ba7b3f</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Sumner P</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0959-535X</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>56dddf17bb2492.81655516</gtr:outcomeId><